    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Phase 2: Structured Teaching and Learning (10 minutes)</title>
        <p>
            <alert>Key Concepts</alert>
        </p>
        <p>
            Two triangles are <alert>similar</alert> if:
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>Their corresponding angles are equal, AND</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Their corresponding sides are in the same ratio.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
            <alert>Enlargement</alert> changes the size of a figure by a <alert>scale factor</alert> while preserving its shape.
        </p>
        <p>
            <alert>Properties of Enlargement:</alert>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>\text{Scale Factor} = \dfrac{\text{Image length}}{\text{Object length}}</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>If scale factor <m>&gt; 1</m>: the image is <alert>larger</alert> than the object.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>If <m>0 &lt; \text{scale factor} &lt; 1</m>: the image is <alert>smaller</alert> than the object.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>If scale factor is <alert>negative</alert>: the image is on the opposite side of the centre and inverted.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
            <alert>Centre of Enlargement:</alert> The point where lines connecting corresponding object and image points intersect.
        </p>
        <p>
            <md>
                <mrow>\frac{OA'}{OA} = \frac{OB'}{OB} = \frac{OC'}{OC} = \frac{A'B'}{AB} = \text{Scale Factor}</mrow>
            </md>
        </p>
    </axiom>

