        <title>Using Similarity to Determine Unknown Lengths and Scale Factor</title>

        <introduction xml:id="auto_9l61wlqo">
            <p xml:id="auto_qlbmy3r0">Load the question by clicking the button below.</p>
        </introduction>

        <stack label="similarity-unknown-lengths-scale" source="stack/top/2-0-Measurement-Geometry/2-1-Similarity-and-Enlargement/2-1-1-Similarity/Using-Similarity-to-Determine-Unknown-Lengths-and-Scale-Factor.xml"/>
    </exercise>

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Phase 4: Independent Practice and Exit Ticket (5 minutes)</title>
        <p>
            <alert>Question 1:</alert> Which triangles are similar? Triangle A has sides 6, 4, 3. Triangle B has sides 24, 16, 12. Triangle C has sides 20, 18, 14.
        </p>
        <p>
            <alert>Answer:</alert> Triangles A and B are similar (ratio <m>= 4</m>). Triangle C is not similar to A or B because the ratios of corresponding sides are not equal.
        </p>
        <p>
            <alert>Question 2:</alert> <m>\triangle ABC \sim \triangle DEF</m>. Given <m>AB = x</m>, <m>BC = 6</m> cm, <m>\angle ABC = 56^\circ</m>, <m>DE = 14</m> cm, <m>EF = 7</m> cm, <m>\angle DEF = \theta</m>. Find <m>\theta</m> and <m>x</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
            <alert>Answer:</alert> Since corresponding angles are equal, <m>\theta = 56^\circ</m>. Using ratios:
            <md>
                <mrow>\frac{BC}{EF} \amp = \frac{AB}{DE}</mrow>
                <mrow>\frac{6}{7} \amp = \frac{x}{14}</mrow>
                <mrow>x \amp = 12 \text{ cm}</mrow>
            </md>
        </p>
        <p>
            <alert>Question 3:</alert> Trapezium <m>TPQRS</m> with <m>TP = 8</m> cm, <m>PQ = 5</m> cm, <m>TS = 16</m> cm, <m>SR = x</m>. Find <m>x</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
            <alert>Answer:</alert>
            <md>
                <mrow>\frac{8}{16} \amp = \frac{5}{x}</mrow>
                <mrow>8x \amp = 80</mrow>
                <mrow>x \amp = 10 \text{ cm}</mrow>
            </md>
        </p>
        <p>
            <alert>Question 4:</alert> <m>\triangle ABE \sim \triangle ACD</m>. Given <m>DC = 24</m> cm, <m>AE = 6</m> cm, <m>ED = 12</m> cm. Find <m>BE</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
            <alert>Answer:</alert> Since <m>AE = 6</m> and <m>ED = 12</m>, then <m>AD = AE + ED = 18</m> cm.
            <md>
                <mrow>\frac{AE}{AD} \amp = \frac{BE}{DC}</mrow>
                <mrow>\frac{6}{18} \amp = \frac{BE}{24}</mrow>
                <mrow>BE \amp = \frac{6 \times 24}{18} = 8 \text{ cm}</mrow>
            </md>
        </p>
    </axiom>
    
