    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Differentiation</title>
        <p>
            <alert>Struggling Learners:</alert>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>Provide pre-drawn triangles so learners can focus on measuring and comparing rather than constructing.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Use colour-coded corresponding sides to make matching easier.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Provide a step-by-step checklist for identifying similar triangles.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
            <alert>On-Level Learners:</alert>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>Complete all practice problems independently.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Explain the concept of similarity to a peer in their own words.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
            <alert>Advanced Learners:</alert>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <alert>Enlargement with coordinates:</alert> Triangle with vertices <m>A(2,3)</m>, <m>B(1,1)</m>, <m>C(4,1)</m> is enlarged with centre at the origin using scale factors <m>2</m>, <m>\frac{1}{2}</m>, and <m>-1</m>. Explore the effect of each scale factor, including negative scale factors.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Apply similarity to map scales and architectural models.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
            <alert>Extension Problems:</alert>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ol markers="1.">
                <li>
                    <p>
                        A photograph is enlarged so that its width increases from <m>10</m> cm to <m>25</m> cm. If the original height is <m>15</m> cm, what is the new height?
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <alert>Answer:</alert> Scale factor <m>= \frac{25}{10} = 2.5</m>. New height <m>= 15 \times 2.5 = 37.5</m> cm.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        A map has a scale of <m>1:50\,000</m>. If the distance between two towns on the map is <m>8</m> cm, what is the actual distance in kilometres?
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <alert>Answer:</alert> Actual distance <m>= 8 \times 50\,000 = 400\,000</m> cm <m>= 4</m> km.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Triangle with vertices <m>X(4,0)</m>, <m>Y(6,3)</m>, <m>Z(5,4)</m> is enlarged with centre <m>(1,1)</m> and scale factor <m>-2</m>. Find the coordinates of the image.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <alert>Answer:</alert>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        For each vertex, apply: <m>\text{Image} = \text{Centre} + \text{SF} \times (\text{Object} - \text{Centre})</m>.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <md>
                            <mrow>X' \amp = (1,1) + (-2)(4-1, 0-1) = (1,1) + (-6, 2) = (-5, 3)</mrow>
                            <mrow>Y' \amp = (1,1) + (-2)(6-1, 3-1) = (1,1) + (-10, -4) = (-9, -3)</mrow>
                            <mrow>Z' \amp = (1,1) + (-2)(5-1, 4-1) = (1,1) + (-8, -6) = (-7, -5)</mrow>
                        </md>
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </axiom>

